Merge pull request #271 from bear/fix-meridian-checks-and-failing-french-tests

Fix failing tests

commit.message:
When 2.6 support was removed I removed the helper function total_seconds()
This changes it back to using the total_seconds() method of the timedelta class

The simple time test was failing for the fr_FR locale because the locale
was setting usesMeridian to True but not defining a meridian string

This caused the CRE_TIME expression to match on an almost everything
because of an earlier change to set meridian to '' instead of None due
to stronger type hinting in Python 3

Fixed by having the _partialParseMeridian() routine to honor if
usesMeridian is set for a local *and* changing the fr_FR local to
set it to False
